Task Manager:

Create a task management system where users can add, update, and delete tasks.
Define a Task class with attributes like title, description, due_date, etc.
Implement methods to add new tasks, update existing tasks, mark tasks as completed, and delete tasks.
You can also add features like sorting tasks by due date, displaying overdue tasks, and saving tasks to a file.
Library Management System:

Build a simple library management system with books, authors, and patrons.
Create classes for Book, Author, and Patron.
Implement methods to check out and return books, view available books, and manage patron information.
Consider using inheritance, for example, creating different types of books (fiction, non-fiction) that inherit from a common Book class.
Store data in a file or database for persistence between program runs.